\begin_body

\begin_layout Title
Thy Lovely Face 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Author
Tim Min
\end_layout

\begin_layout Date
January 28th, 2015
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
thispagestyle{empty}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Note: I wrote a draft for this poem in the winter of 2015.
 I found it on January 17th, 2016 (almost a year later!) and decided to
 complete it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The stars doth gaze upon thy lovely face;
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

They smile upon you with their twinkly shine.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The gentle twinkle give them youthful grace, 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

And yet, what moves me art those eyes of thine.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The seeds of love didst grow beneath our feet.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

So long ago you left, yet still I weep.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The passion in my heart feel bittersweet; 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

For you I sow and sow, yet never reap.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Doth thou not hear the anguish in my call?
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

If thou enjoy my pain, then all is well.
 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

The power is in thou to end this all;
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Three words away from ending living hell.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The dying of the fire would bring relief; 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

But in our youthful love I still believe.
\end_layout

\end_body
